=== Monotonicity analysis ===

For k=2: lcm(n+1,n+2) = (n+1)(n+2) since consecutive integers are coprime
This is strictly increasing in n, so NO collision possible for k=2.

Checking if LCM is strictly increasing for k=3,4,5,6,7,8:
  k=2: STRICTLY INCREASING up to n=5000 (no collision possible in this range)
  k=3: NOT strictly increasing! Examples: [(2, 3, 60, 60), (4, 5, 210, 168), (6, 7, 504, 360)]
  k=4: NOT strictly increasing! Examples: [(1, 2, 60, 60), (4, 5, 840, 504), (7, 8, 3960, 1980)]
  k=5: NOT strictly increasing! Examples: [(0, 1, 60, 60), (4, 5, 2520, 2520), (6, 7, 27720, 3960)]
  k=6: NOT strictly increasing! Examples: [(3, 4, 2520, 2520), (5, 6, 27720, 27720), (8, 9, 180180, 60060)]
  k=7: NOT strictly increasing! Examples: [(2, 3, 2520, 2520), (4, 5, 27720, 27720), (6, 7, 360360, 360360)]
  k=8: NOT strictly increasing! Examples: [(1, 2, 2520, 2520), (3, 4, 27720, 27720), (5, 6, 360360, 360360)]

